body:
This PR brings the project closer to normalizing the tool across platforms.

Previously, this plugin used OS specific calls like rm, mv, curl to complete. These calls have been replaced with platform-agnostic Dart. Additionally, file pathing has been normalized to use Dart's path library.

Issues fixed:
Addresses https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/6052

- [x] I signed the [CLA].

- [x] I updated/added relevant documentation (doc comments with `///`).
- [x] I added new tests to check the change I am making, or this PR is [test-exempt].
- [x] All existing and new tests are passing.

If you need help, consider asking for advice on the #hackers-new channel on [Discord].

commit.message: Add `archive` package to dependencies.

Add `stripComponents` function to util.dart

This function replicates the same behavior as the --strip-components=N flag used in the `tar` command.
Add a platform-agnostic function for extracting content from a tar'd Artifact object.
Throw explicit FileSystemException from `getFileOrThrow`
Use the more specific osError.message and fall back to message if not available.
Implement platform-agnostic zip file extraction.
Indirection function to select the platform specific gradle wrapper.
Refactor _stopDaemon to use gradle selector.
Simplify `runGradleCommand` using a block for version 4.1 and gradle platform selector for all other versions.
extractZip just takes a file path, not an artifact.
Replace calls to `unzip` on OS to a platform-agnostic call.
Replace calls to `tar` on OS to a platform-agnostic call.

Remove redundant code.

Code on line 124 performs the same action, just with a 'rebuildCache' check and directory creation should be handled by our file extraction to extra/empty dir's aren't created needlessly.
Replace `deleteBuildContents` shell call with platform-agnostic call.
Replace `moveToArtifacts` shell call with platform-agnostic call.

Replace `removeAll` shell call with a platform-agnostic version.

Update calling methods.

This and other like methods have the Future signature removed since they all executed using await in any case. Return values are still 'int' to support existing checks.
Add try/catch for `jar` command to notify the user if the shell command is not found.
Add dependency on `http` to support download operations.
Replace shell call to curl with platform-agnostic version.
Rename `curl` to `download`
Fix pathing updates to use platform separators.

Normalize file paths to use OS separators.

Update variable names to make intentions more apparent.
Cleanup and import optimization
Use empty string as default instead of null.

Remove param from _flushToFile

The reference to the accumulator is already available and doesn't need to be passed in each time. Bit easier to read.

title: Plugin tool updates
